 A 29-year-old tricycle rider, Ndubisi Obla, was yesterday arraigned before a Yaba Magistrate’s Court; Lagos for allegedly hitting a man and damaging a vehicle.
The accused was arraigned on a two-count charge of reckless driving and driving without a licence.
The prosecutor, Sergeant Modupe Olaluwoye, told the court that the defendant drove his TVS tricycle with registration number Lagos, EPE 447 QC in a reckless manner on February 2 on Herbert Macaulay Road, Yaba, Lagos.
Olaluwoye said that Obla had driven his tricycle recklessly and hit the first complainant, Mr. Nonso Okolo, who was waiting for a bus on the road.
She said Okolo was seriously injured and had to be taken to the nearest hospital for treatment.
Olaluwoye explained: “My lord, the defendant had also caused damage to a Toyota Corolla car with registration number FKJ 212 CF, belonging to the second complainant, Mr. Chuma Anyoagbunam.”
She added that Obla had driven his tricycle on the highway without a driver’s licence or rider’s card.
Olaluwoye noted that the offences contravened Sections 7 (1), 18 (1) and 19 (1) of the Road Traffic Law of Lagos, 2012.
According to her, Section 19 (1) stipulates a two-year prison term for reckless driving.
However, the accused pleaded not guilty to the charge.
Chief Magistrate Oluwatoyin Oghere granted the defendant bail in the sum of N1 million with two sureties in like sum.
Oghere said the sureties must be gainfully employed and show evidence of three years tax payment to the Lagos State government.